Third Department,

September, 1984

(September 6, 1984) In the Matter of the Claim of Rita Walker, Appellant. Lillian Roberts, as Commissioner of Labor, Respondent.

Motion to dismiss appeal as untimely taken, pursuant to section 624 of the Labor Law, denied, without costs (see Matter of Gonzalez [Ross], 47 NY2d 922; Matter of Krasniqi [Simnica — Ross], 87 AD2d 923). Mahoney, P. J., Kane, Main, Levine and Harvey, JJ., concur.
